    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1990-05-21T22:28:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1990-05-21T22:28:00-05:00" n="130"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d130">
                <head>130. Telegram From the Department of State to the Embassy in the Soviet
                        Union<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d130fn1">Source: Department of State,
                        Central Foreign Policy File, [no film number]. Secret; <gloss
                            target="#t_NIACT_1">Niact</gloss>; Immediate; <gloss target="#t_NODIS_1"
                            >Nodis</gloss>. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_TJ_1"
                        >Timbie</persName>; cleared by <persName corresp="#p_CRA_1"
                            >Clarke</persName> and in <gloss target="#t_OSD_1">OSD</gloss>, <gloss
                            target="#t_JCS_1">JCS</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss>,
                            <gloss target="#t_ACDA_1">ACDA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"
                            >NSC</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_SS_1">S/S</gloss>, and <gloss
                            target="#t_SSO_1">S/S-O</gloss>; approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_VAR_1">Vershbow</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">164262.</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1990-05-22T03:28:00+00:00">May 22, 1990, 0328Z</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Soviet Arms Control Experts Group</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>(S) Entire Text.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Embassy should ask <gloss target="#t_MFA_1">MFA</gloss> for the
                        composition of the Soviet Arms Control Experts Group that is coming to
                        Washington this week pursuant to the agreement between Foreign Minister
                            <persName corresp="#p_SE_1">Shevardnadze</persName> and Secretary
                            <persName corresp="#p_BJA_1">Baker</persName>, and the timing of their
                        arrival and departure.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>We consider this to be a continuation of the <persName corresp="#p_KV_1"
                            >Karpov</persName>-<persName corresp="#p_BR_1">Bartholomew</persName>
                        working group meetings in Moscow. We assume they will continue to address
                        the agenda discussed in Moscow, including the following issues: <list>
                            <label>—</label>
                            <item>Heavy <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">ICBM</gloss>s;</item>
                            <label>—</label>
                            <item>Mobile <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">ICBM</gloss> limits and
                                verification;</item>
                            <label>—</label>
                            <item>Backfire;</item>
                            <label>—</label>
                            <item>Non-circumvention;</item>
                            <label>—</label>
                            <item>
                                <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">ICBM</gloss> warhead sublimit;</item>
                            <label>—</label>
                            <item>Phasing of reductions</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>The group can also consider the bracketed text of the joint statement on
                        future negotiations and <gloss target="#t_PPCM_1">PPCM</gloss>, both of
                        which are now being worked in Geneva.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>In addition, we also look forward to Soviet responses to the <gloss
                            target="#t_CFE_1">CFE</gloss> ideas the US put forward in Moscow.</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>As in Moscow, the purpose of this meeting would be to reach agreements on
                        these issues to recommend to ministers.</item>
                    <label>7.</label>
                    <item>You should confirm that Moscow has the same understanding of the
                        objectives of the experts session as Washington.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJA_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Baker</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
